  <front>
   <head>SONNET TO MRS. BATES.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">O , whose melody the heart obeys,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Thou, who can'st all its subject passions move,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Whose notes to heav'n the list'ning soul can raise,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Can thrill with pity, or can melt with love!</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Happy! whom nature lent this native charm,</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Angelic tones, that shed, with magic power,</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">A sweeter pleasure o'er the social hour:</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The breast to softness soothe, to virtue warm;</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">But yet more happy, that thy life as clear</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">From discord as thy perfect cadence flows;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That, tun'd to sympathy, thy faithful tear</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In mild accordance falls for others' woes;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">That all the tender, pure affections bind,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">In chains of harmony, thy willing mind!</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
